<subSubSection id="C322DBE5FF87FFADFF1ABED862FFFE94" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B87886EFF87FFA3FF1ABED862EAF8A1" blockId="39.[151,1436,1775,1982]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF87FFA3FF1ABED86023F8DD" bold="true" box="[151,297,1775,1802]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130394EBFF87FFA3FEB7BEC76085F8DC" box="[314,399,1776,1803]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="40.[151,250,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1063,1991]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[151,1436,1063,1991]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 36. Records of Indolestes cheesmanae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3342313/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
). This species has been recorded from both 
<collectingCountry id="F32FC8FEFF87FFA3FC0DBEC762D6F8DD" box="[896,988,1776,1802]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F59FFF87FFA3FC66BEC7659DF8DD" author="Kimmins, D." box="[1003,1175,1776,1802]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="68 - 88" refId="ref33337" refString="Kimmins, D. (1936) Odonata, Ephemeroptera and Neuroptera of the New Hebrides and Banks Island. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 10, 18 (103), 68 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933608655175" type="journal article" year="1936">Kimmins 1936</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F59FFF87FFA3FB29BEC76444F8DD" author="Lieftinck, M." box="[1188,1358,1775,1802]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="127 - 166" refId="ref33785" refString="Lieftinck, M. (1975) The dragonflies (Odonata) of New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands - Part 1. Imagines. Cahiers Office de la recherche scientifique et technique outre-mer (ORSTOM), Serie Hydrobiologie, 9, 127 - 166." type="journal article" year="1975">Lieftinck 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F59FFF87FFA3FAD7BEC761DBF8F9" author="Tsuda, S." pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="ref36559" refString="Tsuda, S. (2000) A distributional list of world Odonata. Osaka, Japan, 430 pp." type="book" year="2000">Tsuda 2000</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F32FC8FEFF87FFA3FE9DBF2360B4F8F9" box="[272,446,1812,1838]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
on Grande Terre, with nine known localities from north to south. It has rarely been collected, but we think it has been overlooked due to its cryptic lifestyle and insufficient sampling effort during its flight period. One specimen (unknown locality) is in the 
<collectionCode id="ED2910ABFF87FFA3FC9EBF6B6268F8A1" box="[787,866,1884,1910]" country="New Caledonia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/crvj-94ys" name="Office de la Recherche Scientifique et Technique d'Outre-Mer" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">ONNC</collectionCode>
collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87886EFF87FFA3FF4ABF4865FEF869" blockId="39.[151,1436,1775,1982]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF87FFA3FF4ABF48603FF84D" bold="true" box="[199,309,1919,1946]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Habitats.</emphasis>
The species prefers ponds, grassy marshes, and streams on slopes in forested areas. Ponds are mostly shallow, and may partially dry out seasonally. It has similar habitat preferences to 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F3EDFF87FFA3FBA3BF9265E7F869" authorityName="Hagen in Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1862" box="[1070,1261,1957,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concinnus">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF87FFA3FBA3BF9265E7F869" box="[1070,1261,1957,1982]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Lestes concinnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF47D8E6FF88FFACFF1ABC37635EFBCE" box="[151,596,1024,1049]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3342311/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" startId="40.[151,250,1024,1049]" targetBox="[151,1436,151,1004]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="8B87886EFF88FFACFF1ABC37635EFBCE" blockId="40.[151,596,1024,1049]" box="[151,596,1024,1049]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF88FFACFF1ABC37602AFBCE" bold="true" box="[151,288,1024,1049]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">FIGURE 35.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C38F3EDFF88FFACFEABBC366305FBCE" baseAuthorityName="Kimmins" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[294,527,1025,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Indolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cheesmanae">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF88FFACFEABBC366305FBCE" box="[294,527,1025,1049]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Indolestes cheesmanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF47D8E6FF88FFACFF1ABFED6380F825" box="[151,650,2010,2035]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3342313/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" startId="40.[151,250,2010,2035]" targetBox="[151,1436,1063,1991]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="8B87886EFF88FFACFF1ABFED6380F825" blockId="40.[151,650,2010,2035]" box="[151,650,2010,2035]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF88FFACFF1ABFED602AF824" bold="true" box="[151,288,2010,2035]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">FIGURE 36.</emphasis>
Records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F3EDFF88FFACFE16BFEC638EF824" baseAuthorityName="Kimmins" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[411,644,2011,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Indolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cheesmanae">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF88FFACFE16BFEC638EF824" box="[411,644,2011,2035]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Indolestes cheesmanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B87886EFF89FFADFF4AB8AF6225FF00" blockId="41.[151,1437,152,323]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF89FFADFF4AB8AF60D0FF64" bold="true" box="[199,474,152,179]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Biology and behaviour.</emphasis>
Its larvae are unknown but 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F59FFF89FFADFC9CB8AE62C3FF63" author="Lieftinck, M." box="[785,969,153,180]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="127 - 171" refId="ref33696" refString="Lieftinck, M. (1960) Consideration on the genus Lestes Leach with notes on the classification and description of new Indo-Australian species and larval forms (Odonata, Lestidae). Nova Guinea, Zoology, 8, 127 - 171." type="journal article" year="1960">Lieftinck (1960)</bibRefCitation>
considered that they should be very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F3EDFF89FFADFF55B8896221FF00" authority="Hagen in Selys-Longchamps, 1862" authorityName="Hagen in Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1862" box="[216,811,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concinnus">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF89FFADFF55B889609DFF00" box="[216,407,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Lestes concinnus</emphasis>
Hagen in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F59FFF89FFADFD86B88A6221FF00" author="Selys-Longchamps, E. de" box="[523,811,189,215]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="288 - 331" refId="ref35767" refString="Selys-Longchamps, E. de. (1862) Synopsis des Agrionines. 2 me Legion: Lestes. Bulletins de L'Academie Royale des sciences, des lettres et des Beaux-Arts de Belgique, 2 eme Serie, 13, 288 - 331." type="journal article" year="1862">Selys-Longchamps, 1862</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87886EFF89FFADFF4AB8D762FFFE94" blockId="41.[151,1437,152,323]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF89FFADFF4AB8D76013FF2C" bold="true" box="[199,281,224,251]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Status.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C38F3EDFF89FFADFEAEB8D66322FF2C" baseAuthorityName="Kimmins" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[291,552,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Indolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cheesmanae">
<emphasis id="B94C547CFF89FFADFEAEB8D66322FF2C" box="[291,552,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Indolestes cheesmanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a regional endemic from both 
<collectingCountry id="F32FC8FEFF89FFADFC3EB8D66505FF2C" box="[947,1039,225,251]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F32FC8FEFF89FFADFBC0B8D6640BFF2C" box="[1101,1281,225,251]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. Its preferred habitats are vanishing following disappearance of coastal marshes (especially in Nouméa and its surroundings) and drainage of other marshy areas. We consider this species as vulnerable (VU).
</paragraph>
